Enum BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type>
      • com.idevicesinc.sweetblue.BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    UsesCustomNull, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type>
    Enclosing interface:
    BleDevice.ReadWriteListener

    public static enum BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type
extends java.lang.Enum<BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type>
implements UsesCustomNull
    The type of operation for a BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.ReadWriteEvent - read, write, poll, etc.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DISABLING_NOTIFICATION
      Opposite of ENABLING_NOTIFICATION.
      ENABLING_NOTIFICATION
      Associated with BleDevice.enableNotify(UUID, ReadWriteListener) and called when enabling the notification completes by writing to the Descriptor of the given UUID.
      INDICATION
      Similar to NOTIFICATION, kicked off from BleDevice.enableNotify(UUID, ReadWriteListener), but under the hood this is treated slightly differently.
      NOTIFICATION
      Associated with BleDevice.enableNotify(UUID, ReadWriteListener) when we actually get a notification.
      NULL
      As of now, only used for BleDevice.ConnectionFailListener.ConnectionFailEvent.txnFailReason() in some cases.
      POLL
      Associated with BleDevice.startPoll(UUID, Interval, ReadWriteListener) or BleDevice.startRssiPoll(Interval, ReadWriteListener).
      PSUEDO_NOTIFICATION
      Associated with BleDevice.startChangeTrackingPoll(UUID, Interval, ReadWriteListener) or BleDevice.enableNotify(UUID, Interval, ReadWriteListener) where a force-read timeout is invoked.
      READ
      Associated with BleDevice.read(UUID, ReadWriteListener) or BleDevice.readRssi(ReadWriteListener).
      WRITE
      Associated with BleDevice.write(UUID, byte[]) or BleDevice.write(UUID, byte[], ReadWriteListener) or BleDevice.setMtu(int) or BleDevice.setName(String, UUID, ReadWriteListener).
      WRITE_NO_RESPONSE
      Similar to WRITE but under the hood BluetoothGattCharacteristic.WRITE_TYPE_NO_RESPONSE is used.
      WRITE_SIGNED
      Similar to WRITE but under the hood BluetoothGattCharacteristic.WRITE_TYPE_SIGNED is used.

      • ENABLING_NOTIFICATION

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type ENABLING_NOTIFICATION
        Associated with BleDevice.enableNotify(UUID, ReadWriteListener) and called when enabling the notification completes by writing to the Descriptor of the given UUID. BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Status.SUCCESS doesn't necessarily mean that notifications will definitely now work (there may be other issues in the underlying stack), but it's a reasonable guarantee.

      • DISABLING_NOTIFICATION

        public static final BleDevice.ReadWriteListener.Type DISABLING_NOTIFICATION
        Opposite of ENABLING_NOTIFICATION.

        public final boolean isRead()

      • isNativeNotification

        public final boolean isNativeNotification()
        Subset of isNotification(), returns true only for NOTIFICATION and INDICATION, i.e. only notifications who origin is an *actual* notification (or indication) sent from the remote BLE device.
